OL,5,CKaba
OL,7,FBut the defendant told the court he
OL,8,Fgenuinely believed one of his
OL,9,Fcolleagues was about to die, and the
OL,10,Fonly way he had to negate the threat
OL,11,Fwas to shoot Mr Kaba.
OL,13,FA fellow firearms officer known as
OL,14,FDS87 said he would have taken a shot
OL,15,Fif Blake had not, and another
OL,16,Fidentified by the cypher E156 said he
OL,17,Fwas "fractions of a second" away from
OL,18,Fdoing the same.
